# Methodology — Dealer Performance Intelligence System

## Research Objective
To build an AI-powered dealer performance monitoring system that not only identifies underperforming dealers but explains why and recommends specific interventions.

## Data Generation
- Synthetic dataset generated using Python with NumPy and Pandas
- 500 dealers, 24 months, 11 KPIs, 12,000 total rows
- Seed 42 for reproducibility
- Realistic patterns: seasonality, gradual decline, sudden anomalies

## Composite Scoring Engine
- All 11 KPIs normalized to 0-100 scale
- Weighted average based on business importance
- Negative KPIs (CPTV, TAT) reverse-normalized

## Anomaly Detection
- Algorithm: Isolation Forest
- Contamination rate: 5%
- Features: All 11 KPIs + composite score

## Explainability (XAI)
- Model: XGBoost Classifier
- Explanation method: SHAP (SHapley Additive exPlanations)
- Output: Feature importance ranking, summary plots

## Counterfactual Recommendations
- Library: DiCE (Diverse Counterfactual Explanations)
- Base model: Random Forest Classifier
- Output: Minimal changes required to flip anomaly → normal

## Dashboard
- Tool: Power BI Desktop
- Pages: 5 (Executive Summary, Dealer Deep Dive, Dealer Comparison, Anomaly Center, AI Assistant)

## Web Application
- Framework: Streamlit
- AI Model: Google Gemini 2.0 Flash
- Hosting: Streamlit Community Cloud

